item.title: Can you do a "Heavy" / Thrash track? LOL
item.dc:creator: Devoid-of-joy
item.description:
Oh yeah! The creepier the better I say. Terror is the tone I gear towards, kind of like the mentality of horror films. I’m behind in the gaming world these days but the the feeling you get when something as as harmless as a horror game or a creepy song is what I strive towards.
I wish I could just do EDM, future bass, or any popular genre but it’s just not in my blood I guess. Definitely would be a more profitable endevour.

item.title: Can you do a "Heavy" / Thrash track? LOL
item.dc:creator: NEWNAMES
item.description:
@Southborne
Definitions of Thrash: (thanks to the google dictionary and a few personal edits by me)

  1. to beat (a person or animal) repeatedly and violently with a stick or whip… well that’s pleasant…
  2. a violent or noisy movement, typically involving hitting something repeatedly… again, well that’s pleasant…
  3. a style of fast, loud, harsh-sounding rock music, combining elements of punk and heavy metal… so imo none of these tracks sound like thrash…
